channel.title: RSLoader
channel.description:
Credits: -Ppls - Giving me lots and lots of little tips always <3 edit: giving me WHOLE IDEA behind this loader (pls no shootin) -Newbiehacker - This guy is the best ever, no word can describe him. -Ollie - i made most of the loader bits
What it Does: - this is no normal generic loader, this has a canvas hack so it is possible for you to minimise the client and still obtain the image onscreen from it, this was possible by hacking the runescape canvas class, and as far as i am aware, undetectably.
Download: - http://rapidshare.com/files/30366009/RS.rar - Note: Download as a Free User Please :)
i decided to release because i want to see more people making bots, so i can have a choice in using them :P i cba to maintain my own

item.description:
@moparisthebest wrote:

[quote=“ruler, post:27, topic:90938”][quote author=Moparisthebest link=topic=132641.msg1286893#msg1286893 date=1178676674]

to taios, all of the other loaders don’t work (as far as i know)

Cherokee still works and has yet to break.
[/quote]
mis-represention. It requires a config file where a user has to hand key the stub. Has to hand key the server. It is not dynamic.[/quote]

Cherokee is a framework where the user implements two interfaces to load any applet in the world, so you can do it any way your heart desires, you simply have to tell Cherokee what class implements the Setup interface.

item.title: RSLoader
item.dc:creator: @pplsuqbawlz pplsuqbawlz
item.description:
@pplsuqbawlz wrote:

[quote=“frank_, post:13, topic:90938”][quote author=popcorn89 link=topic=132641.msg1284369#msg1284369 date=1178612845]

This isn’t a Java Agent = fail.

Lolol.

Requires a web browser = fail
[/quote]you can use a javaagent in a loader == win too

[quote author=the bomb 454 link=topic=132641.msg1284580#msg1284580 date=1178619121]
to regecks, it allows you to minimize the window and if you have a bot running it can still do things.
[/quote]i am guessing that you are implying that the bot must be colour based[/quote]
The point of the matter is, I’m glad some of you have figured out how to use the java agent abstract layer; but it’s not the way it should go and is by FAR inefficient; The caching is simple jar’s storage over-writing (except in ms jvms etc blah) is rather minimalistic. Now caching and unpacking data in a JVM that has all the information (previously) loaded; and up-kept allows for massive amount of block sharing (Amongst other things). Not to mention the 64 (firefox) to 128-256 (internet explorer) megabytes of “tack-on” java-agent-applet jackets add.

Win’s vs. losses, JA loses.

Read full topic
